<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1010,1899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1154,1179]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1907" box="[339,581,1154,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Miocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybea">
<emphasis box="[339,581,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Miocephala chalybea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the type species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1907" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1907" box="[831,1126,1154,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Miocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[831,965,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Miocephala</emphasis>
Konow, 1907
</taxonomicName>
, which is treated today as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrank, 1802" authorityName="Schrank" authorityYear="1802" box="[291,517,1190,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,344,1191,1214]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Arge</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schrank, F. von" box="[352,517,1190,1215]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" refId="ref19295" refString="Schrank, F. von P. (1802) Fauna Boica. Durchgedachte Geschichte der in Baiern einheimischen und zahmen Thiere. Zweiter Band. Zweite Abtheilung. Bey Johann Wilhelm Krull, Ingolstadt, 412 pp." type="book" year="1802">Schrank, 1802</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Already its original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, F. W." box="[921,1099,1190,1215]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" pagination="161 - 174" refId="ref17981" refString="Konow, F. W. (1907 b) Neue Chalastogastra aus den naturhist. Museen in Hamburg und Madrid. Zeitschrift fur systematische Hymenopterologie und Dipterologie, 7 (2), 161 - 174." type="journal article" year="1907">Konow (1907b)</bibRefCitation>
caused some confusion. Both sexes of the taxon were described, but he mentioned only for the female: “Die weibliche Type ist Eigentum des National-Museums in 
<collectingRegion box="[402,487,1262,1287]" country="Spain" name="Madrid" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Madrid</collectingRegion>
” [translated: ‘The female type is property of the National Museum in Madrid’]. The deposition of the male type(s) was not mentioned, and therefore it is to be expected in Konow's collection (today at SDEI). Konow’s note about the female type cannot be interpreted as a designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[1121,1223,1334,1359]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">holotype</typeStatus>
. A male labeled by Konow is housed in the SDEI collection, and this specimen seems to be the only specimen of the species that was examined by subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Malaise, R." box="[529,699,1406,1431]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" pagination="47 - 59" refId="ref18452" refString="Malaise, R. (1937 a) Old and new genera of Arginae (Hymen. Tenthred.). Entomologisk Tidskrift, 58 (1 - 2), 47 - 59." type="journal article" year="1937">Malaise 1937a</bibRefCitation>
: “the type... 
<taxonomicName authority="Knw" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1907" box="[839,1138,1406,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Miocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybea">Miocephala chalybea Knw</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[1146,1169,1406,1431]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
”; 
<bibRefCitation author="Oehlke, J. &amp; Wudowenz, J." pageId="10" pageNumber="113" pagination="363 - 420" refId="ref18738" refString="Oehlke, J. &amp; Wudowenz, J. (1984) Katalog der in den Sammlungen der Abteilung Taxonomie der Insekten des Institutes fur Pflanzenschutzforschung, Bereich Eberswalde (ehemals Deutsches Entomologisches Institut), aufbewahrten Typen - XXII (Hymenoptera: Symphyta). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 34 (2), 363 - 420." type="journal article" year="1984">Oehlke &amp; Wudowenz 1984</bibRefCitation>
: “ 
<specimenCount box="[238,282,1442,1467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" type="male">1 ♂</specimenCount>
, 
<typeStatus box="[296,406,1442,1467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Syntypus</typeStatus>
”; 
<bibRefCitation author="Saini, M. S. &amp; Thind, A. S." box="[429,662,1442,1467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" pagination="71 - 111" refId="ref19125" refString="Saini, M. S. &amp; Thind, A. S. (1995) Revision of genus Arge Schrank from India (Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Argidae). Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift, Neue Folge, 42 (1), 71 - 111. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 19950420109" type="journal article" year="1995">Saini &amp; Thind 1995</bibRefCitation>
: “ 
<typeStatus box="[685,794,1442,1467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Holotype</typeStatus>
, Coll. Konow ... 
<specimenCount box="[985,1008,1442,1467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
”). Futhermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Saini, M. S. &amp; Thind, A. S." box="[1189,1436,1442,1467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" pagination="71 - 111" refId="ref19125" refString="Saini, M. S. &amp; Thind, A. S. (1995) Revision of genus Arge Schrank from India (Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Argidae). Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift, Neue Folge, 42 (1), 71 - 111. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 19950420109" type="journal article" year="1995">Saini &amp; Thind (1995)</bibRefCitation>
claimed that the female of the species is unknown. All other mentions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1907" box="[1031,1132,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Miocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybea">
<emphasis box="[1031,1132,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">chalybea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seem to be based not on examined material, but on the papers cited above. Konow’s redescription (
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, F. W." box="[1009,1173,1514,1539]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" pagination="145 - 160" refId="ref18090" refString="Konow, F. W. (1907 e) Systematische Zusammenstellung der bisher bekannt gewordenen Chalastogastra (Hymenopterorum subordo tertius). Zeitschrift fur systematische Hymenopterologie und Dipterologie, 7 (5), 417 - 432 [= 2, 145 - 160]." type="journal article" year="1907">Konow 1907e</bibRefCitation>
) is a translation of the Latin original description into German.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1010,1899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">
There are some discrepancies between the description and the available material. These concern primarily the coloration of the hind tibiae, that should be yellow (“tibiis posticis flavis”), and the body color, that should be black-blue (“nigro-coerulea”). In the male specimen the hind tibiae are very dark brown to black, and the thorax dorsally has a strong greenish tinge. On the other hand there is no doubt that the specimen is one of the 
<typeStatus box="[1331,1432,1695,1719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">syntypes</typeStatus>
, and Konow’s description regarding the male is inaccurate. The question, if the 
<specimenCount box="[1057,1225,1730,1755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
are conspecific or not, must be left unanswered. It seems not unlikely that they represent the same species, but more specimens are needed to prove this assumption. As all subsequent papers about the status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1907" box="[1032,1166,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Miocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1166,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Miocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1907" box="[1221,1322,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Miocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybea">
<emphasis box="[1221,1322,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">chalybea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are based on the male, this specimen was selected as 
<typeStatus box="[639,745,1838,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">lectotype</typeStatus>
, even if the description of the species does not completely fit the type specimen.
</paragraph>
